-What?

564
00:43:26,610 --> 00:43:29,610
Hey, Lee Yonggu.
Are you taking his side already?

565
00:43:30,860 --> 00:43:34,240
Shall we have your son-in-law
pour us a drink?

566
00:43:34,320 --> 00:43:35,490
-Yes.
-Sounds good.

567
00:43:37,120 --> 00:43:37,950
I'll pour it for you.

568
00:43:38,030 --> 00:43:39,040
-What?
-What?

569
00:43:39,120 --> 00:43:42,210
Not you. Yonggu's son-in-law.

570
00:43:43,040 --> 00:43:44,120
Go ahead.

571
00:43:50,710 --> 00:43:52,470
You should pour it for your father first.

572
00:43:52,920 --> 00:43:54,220
Yes, sir.

573
00:43:54,840 --> 00:43:55,930
Gosh, what is he doing?

574
00:43:56,430 --> 00:43:57,550
I have some already.

575
00:43:59,100 --> 00:44:00,100
Yes, sir.

576
00:44:02,890 --> 00:44:04,270
He's pouring you makgeolli.

577
00:44:05,850 --> 00:44:07,190
He's good at figuring people out.

578
00:44:10,650 --> 00:44:12,990
Hey, don't shake it. You'll spill it.

579
00:44:13,070 --> 00:44:14,240
But I didn't shake--

580
00:44:14,320 --> 00:44:15,820
All right. Good.

581
00:44:16,780 --> 00:44:19,700
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

582
00:44:26,290 --> 00:44:27,290
Here you go.

583
00:44:27,540 --> 00:44:28,540
Here you go.

584
00:44:28,790 --> 00:44:29,630
Here you go.

585
00:44:31,460 --> 00:44:32,380
Take it.

586
00:44:38,800 --> 00:44:39,800
Take it.

587
00:44:40,720 --> 00:44:41,850
He can't drink.

588
00:44:41,930 --> 00:44:43,930
-What?
-Hey, Sina.

589
00:44:44,140 --> 00:44:46,350
Are you taking
your husband's side already?

590
00:44:49,810 --> 00:44:50,730
No, it's not like that.

591
00:44:51,730 --> 00:44:53,440
Would you like anything else?

592
00:44:53,530 --> 00:44:55,030
-Oh, we're out of water.
-Water.

593
00:44:55,110 --> 00:44:56,650
-We'll go get some water.
-Yes, water.

594
00:44:57,240 --> 00:44:58,110
-Water.
-Water.

595
00:44:58,200 --> 00:45:00,910
-Water.
-Look at those two. Jeez.

596
00:45:01,580 --> 00:45:03,330
Doesn't he look so much like Noh Gojin?

597
00:45:03,410 --> 00:45:05,710
Wow, this snack is so delicious.

598
00:45:06,290 --> 00:45:08,370
He totally…Oh, it's delicious.

599
00:45:08,460 --> 00:45:09,580
-Isn't it?
-Yes.

600
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:11,670
Water!

601
00:45:11,750 --> 00:45:14,340
First, pour a drink for everyone.

602
00:45:14,590 --> 00:45:17,590
When everyone gets drunk after that,
we can just leave.

603
00:45:21,010 --> 00:45:23,850
-Okay, cheers!
-Cheers!

604
00:45:28,940 --> 00:45:30,060
Gosh, this is great.

605
00:45:33,270 --> 00:45:34,400
-All right!
-Great!

606
00:45:36,070 --> 00:45:38,950
He can drink after all.

607
00:45:39,030 --> 00:45:40,160
Let me pour you one.

608
00:45:40,240 --> 00:45:41,660
Cheers!

609
00:45:43,200 --> 00:45:45,370
Hey, what's that?

610
00:45:45,450 --> 00:45:47,750
No, it's really okay.

611
00:45:47,830 --> 00:45:49,170
-Gosh.
-Drink up.

612
00:45:50,500 --> 00:45:53,250
-Drink up.
-Drink up all the way.

613
00:45:53,880 --> 00:45:54,920
Drink up. Come on.

614
00:45:56,550 --> 00:45:57,550
-Oh, gosh!
-What?

615
00:45:57,630 --> 00:45:58,630
What's wrong?

616
00:46:02,300 --> 00:46:05,220
I feel so bad for these crabs.

617
00:46:05,310 --> 00:46:07,560
-What's wrong with you?
-You startled me!

618
00:46:08,060 --> 00:46:09,520
-Jeez.
-What is she talking about?

619
00:46:10,730 --> 00:46:12,900
-My goodness!
-My goodness! He can really drink.

620
00:46:12,980 --> 00:46:14,020
He can really drink.

621
00:46:14,110 --> 00:46:16,980
Yonggu's son-in-law
certainly doesn't disappoint.

622
00:46:17,070 --> 00:46:19,530
Yonggu's son-in-law indeed.

623
00:46:19,610 --> 00:46:20,990
For Yonggu's son-in-law.

624
00:46:21,070 --> 00:46:23,070
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

625
00:46:23,160 --> 00:46:24,120
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

626
00:46:44,010 --> 00:46:46,430
-If I long for you
-If I long for you

627
00:46:46,510 --> 00:46:50,270
-Maybe I'll get to see you again one day
-Maybe I'll get to see you again one day

628
00:46:50,480 --> 00:46:54,150
-Like in movies
-I need more snacks.

629
00:46:54,230 --> 00:46:57,320
-I hope miracles like that happen…
-Otherwise, my stomach will hurt.

630
00:46:57,400 --> 00:47:00,400
Yonggu's son-in-law, come join us.

631
00:47:00,490 --> 00:47:01,820
Yes, come join us.

632
00:47:01,900 --> 00:47:03,780
My goodness. Yonggu's son-in-law's here.

633
00:47:03,860 --> 00:47:05,320
-Join us.
-Drink with us.

634
00:47:05,410 --> 00:47:07,410
-Give him a drink.
-Have one more drink.

635
00:47:07,490 --> 00:47:10,870
-Next year's potato farming…
-That's what I'm saying.

636
00:47:10,960 --> 00:47:12,670
You just need to do it.

637
00:47:12,750 --> 00:47:14,380
-Okay.
-But…

638
00:47:14,460 --> 00:47:17,630
potatoes didn't grow well in our town,
so I didn't get to eat any.

639
00:47:17,710 --> 00:47:20,380
So you need to grow them, okay?

640
00:47:20,460 --> 00:47:22,090
That's it, okay?

641
00:47:22,170 --> 00:47:23,470
Gosh, it's not like that.

642
00:47:23,550 --> 00:47:25,680
Oh, you're here!

643
00:47:25,760 --> 00:47:27,680
-I brought this.
-All right!

644
00:47:28,260 --> 00:47:29,930
-Wow!
-All right!

645
00:47:30,020 --> 00:47:32,140
You brought such a precious drink.

646
00:47:32,230 --> 00:47:34,600
-Dad!
-Wow!

647
00:47:36,730 --> 00:47:37,730
Now.

648
00:48:00,460 --> 00:48:03,800
Here, here. Guess what I got!

649
00:48:05,840 --> 00:48:08,050
All right!

650
00:48:08,180 --> 00:48:09,640
Drink!

651
00:48:28,120 --> 00:48:29,780
Those people are like leeches.

652
00:48:36,080 --> 00:48:37,170
Number 5938!

653
00:48:38,170 --> 00:48:41,300
Number 5938! Pull over to the right.

654
00:48:41,920 --> 00:48:42,920
Me?

655
00:48:43,710 --> 00:48:45,300
Me? Why?

656
00:49:04,990 --> 00:49:06,030
May I help you?

657
00:49:08,160 --> 00:49:11,660
You can't drive so fast on a country road.

658
00:49:13,620 --> 00:49:14,750
Gosh, you reek of alcohol.

659
00:49:22,750 --> 00:49:23,750
Turn off the engine.

660
00:49:32,600 --> 00:49:33,470
So you didn't drink.

661
00:49:34,060 --> 00:49:34,890
See?

662
00:49:35,890 --> 00:49:37,770
I told you I didn't drink.

663
00:49:37,850 --> 00:49:40,190
But you still reek of alcohol.

664
00:49:43,520 --> 00:49:46,070
Where were you in this neighborhood?

665
00:49:46,780 --> 00:49:47,820
Sorry?

666
00:49:47,900 --> 00:49:50,910
SUPERMARKET

667
00:49:50,990 --> 00:49:52,870
I'm exhausted.

668
00:49:54,490 --> 00:49:56,000
He should've gotten back safely, right?

669
00:50:02,710 --> 00:50:03,710
Hello?

670
00:50:05,630 --> 00:50:06,460
What?

671
00:50:06,550 --> 00:50:10,050
I was trying so hard
not to drink there by doing this.

672
00:50:10,130 --> 00:50:11,760
-That's why I smell like…
-But look!

673
00:50:11,840 --> 00:50:13,850
Please stop! What's wrong with you?

674
00:50:14,810 --> 00:50:16,220
Who are you?

675
00:50:16,850 --> 00:50:18,350
I'm his guardian.

676
00:50:27,990 --> 00:50:30,910
It's all a lie when they say
that people are nicer in the countryside.

677
00:50:31,410 --> 00:50:33,370
They even detained an innocent person.

678
00:50:35,450 --> 00:50:38,870
Yes, people are cold-hearted
in the countryside,

679
00:50:38,950 --> 00:50:40,210
so go back to Seoul now.

680
00:50:43,330 --> 00:50:44,290
I'll go now.

681
00:51:00,350 --> 00:51:02,270
PLEASE REFUEL

682
00:51:10,030 --> 00:51:11,030
What's wrong?

683
00:51:21,500 --> 00:51:24,290
I'm out of gas.

684
00:51:33,260 --> 00:51:36,010
Since it's late,
let's go back to my house for now.

685
00:51:38,850 --> 00:51:40,270
How do we get there?

686
00:52:05,210 --> 00:52:06,920
I'm his guardian.

687
00:52:11,010 --> 00:52:12,090
Guardian?

688
00:52:12,880 --> 00:52:14,260
How ridiculous.

689
00:53:43,560 --> 00:53:46,640
We best get some sleep here
and head out early in the morning.

690
00:53:46,930 --> 00:53:48,140
Sleep here?

691
00:53:49,770 --> 00:53:52,270
Or what? Sleep on the streets?

692
00:54:01,160 --> 00:54:03,200
They're all good people.

693
00:54:06,200 --> 00:54:07,500
My dad's friends.

694
00:54:09,210 --> 00:54:12,330
They don't just offer drinks to whomever.

695
00:54:13,420 --> 00:54:15,300
It was because
it was my mom's death anniversary.

696
00:54:17,760 --> 00:54:21,680
That's just how they console my dad.

697
00:54:22,760 --> 00:54:25,310
So please don't think poorly of them.

698
00:54:48,160 --> 00:54:50,160
REST IN PEACE

699
00:55:24,950 --> 00:55:28,410
When did your mother

700
00:55:29,660 --> 00:55:30,660
pass away?

701
00:55:32,250 --> 00:55:33,670
When I was 12.

702
00:55:39,920 --> 00:55:41,170
You were very young

703
00:55:41,970 --> 00:55:42,970
like me.

704
00:55:56,770 --> 00:55:57,860
You must've

705
00:55:59,820 --> 00:56:01,070
been scared too.

706
00:56:31,350 --> 00:56:33,270
Oh, my car.

707
00:56:43,320 --> 00:56:44,320
Hello?

708
00:56:44,860 --> 00:56:47,660
I put gas in Mr. Noh Manners' car.

709
00:56:47,740 --> 00:56:50,660
What? How did you know?

710
00:56:50,740 --> 00:56:53,160
My youngest aunt's husband is
a police officer, you know?

711
00:56:53,250 --> 00:56:55,330
He's sorry he didn't realize
it was the son-in-law.

712
00:56:57,750 --> 00:57:00,840
I loaded your dad's gifts too,
so head up first.

713
00:57:00,920 --> 00:57:02,340
Talk to you later.

714
00:57:04,840 --> 00:57:05,800
Gifts?

715
00:57:06,800 --> 00:57:08,390
What's all this?

716
00:57:15,890 --> 00:57:18,850
Why are all these potatoes in my car?

717
00:57:21,770 --> 00:57:24,780
I put them in there.

718
00:57:25,690 --> 00:57:28,070
We have to take home
some regional specialty products.

719
00:57:29,200 --> 00:57:30,240
Get in.

720
00:57:31,660 --> 00:57:32,490
Wait.

721
00:57:32,580 --> 00:57:33,790
But,

722
00:57:33,870 --> 00:57:35,330
how do I even sit?

723
00:57:48,760 --> 00:57:51,390
My car… Please pull over.

724
00:57:52,470 --> 00:57:53,310
Why?

725
00:57:53,390 --> 00:57:55,930
Let's toss these potatoes.

726
00:57:57,890 --> 00:57:59,650
-Excuse me?
-Let's just toss them.

727
00:58:00,310 --> 00:58:02,940
Why do I have to suffer
because of these potatoes?

728
00:58:03,020 --> 00:58:08,200
And because of the dirt from the boxes,
my car is totally ruined now.

729
00:58:08,860 --> 00:58:12,120
Do you even know how hard farmers work
to grow these potatoes?

730
00:58:12,200 --> 00:58:14,790
They may not seem much to you,
they're very precious crops.

731
00:58:14,870 --> 00:58:16,660
That's not my problem.

732
00:58:17,450 --> 00:58:20,790
I can't drive to Seoul like this,
and frankly, I don't want to.

733
00:58:21,250 --> 00:58:22,250
And…

734
00:58:23,000 --> 00:58:25,000
even if you were to offer
1,000 boxes of potatoes,

735
00:58:25,460 --> 00:58:27,260
you can't buy this car.

736
00:58:27,550 --> 00:58:29,130
Then which is the rational choice?

737
00:58:29,720 --> 00:58:31,680
Even a three-year-old
would know the answer.

738
00:58:35,430 --> 00:58:36,640
Gosh, darn it.

739
00:59:13,390 --> 00:59:14,680
She finally gets it.

740
00:59:15,180 --> 00:59:17,350
This is the rational choice.

741
00:59:18,220 --> 00:59:19,430
It's so much better.

742
00:59:20,560 --> 00:59:22,390
Okay, let's go now.

743
00:59:29,190 --> 00:59:31,110
What are you doing? Aren't you getting in?

744
00:59:31,530 --> 00:59:32,530
No.

745
00:59:33,280 --> 00:59:34,160
Why not?

746
00:59:34,240 --> 00:59:37,950
To transport my potatoes,
this darn car is too crappy.

747
00:59:39,620 --> 00:59:42,250
-What did you say?
-I'm not throwing away the potatoes.

748
00:59:42,330 --> 00:59:44,250
I'm throwing away this worthless car.

749
00:59:44,920 --> 00:59:47,420
Even if you were to offer me
1,000 truckloads of these darn cars,

750
00:59:48,300 --> 00:59:50,840
I wouldn't exchange them for my potatoes.

751
00:59:52,130 --> 00:59:53,430
So go back on your own.

752
01:00:04,440 --> 01:00:06,770
TAXI

753
01:00:06,860 --> 01:00:08,860
POTATO

754
01:00:15,950 --> 01:00:16,950
Thank you.

755
01:00:23,250 --> 01:00:24,250
-Thank you.
-No problem.

756
01:00:25,960 --> 01:00:26,960
-Bye, sir.
-Bye.

757
01:00:29,750 --> 01:00:30,840
Wait, sir.

758
01:00:30,920 --> 01:00:32,800
Please take this.

759
01:00:32,880 --> 01:00:34,170
You really don't have to.

760
01:00:34,260 --> 01:00:36,640
-Thank you for the potatoes.
-Bye.

761
01:00:45,940 --> 01:00:47,480
Please take these potatoes!

762
01:00:47,560 --> 01:00:50,520
Pesticide-free potatoes
that my dad grew himself!

763
01:00:50,610 --> 01:00:53,690
They're very sweet and delicious.
Please take a box. Okay?

764
01:00:53,780 --> 01:00:54,780
-They're free.
-Really?

765
01:00:54,860 --> 01:00:56,240
-Can we take a box?
-Yes, you can.

766
01:00:56,740 --> 01:00:59,870
They're very sweet and delicious.
Cook them and enjoy.

767
01:00:59,950 --> 01:01:00,990
-Enjoy!
-Thank you.

768
01:01:01,540 --> 01:01:02,870
Please take these potatoes.

769
01:01:02,950 --> 01:01:04,660
They're free. Pesticide-free potatoes.

770
01:01:04,750 --> 01:01:06,210
-Thank you.
-Enjoy.

771
01:01:06,710 --> 01:01:08,540
Free potatoes over here!
Would you like some?

772
01:01:08,630 --> 01:01:09,710
-Are they really free?
-Yes.

773
01:01:09,790 --> 01:01:10,750
-One box, please.
-Okay.

774
01:01:37,150 --> 01:01:40,200
What? Are potatoes
more important than people?

775
01:01:40,660 --> 01:01:42,160
People are more important.

776
01:01:43,240 --> 01:01:47,000
Why did she get so upset
for throwing away some potatoes?

777
01:02:13,520 --> 01:02:16,150
I'm sure she already left by now.
She wouldn't still be here.

778
01:02:39,300 --> 01:02:40,300
Hello? Mom?

779
01:02:41,260 --> 01:02:43,510
Me? I'm out making deliveries.

780
01:02:44,550 --> 01:02:46,890
It's not hard. Not at all.

781
01:02:47,720 --> 01:02:49,940
How about you, Mom? Is your knee okay?

782
01:02:51,270 --> 01:02:53,560
Make sure you go see the doctor, okay?

783
01:02:54,150 --> 01:02:55,320
I'll come home this weekend.

784
01:02:55,820 --> 01:02:57,610
I want to eat your kimchi stew.

785
01:02:58,320 --> 01:03:00,950
Mom, I have to go now.
I'll call you again later, okay?

786
01:04:01,800 --> 01:04:02,970
I felt wronged.

787
01:04:04,550 --> 01:04:05,550
Why…

788
01:04:07,100 --> 01:04:09,350
Why was I the only one
who had to die like this?

789
01:04:12,350 --> 01:04:13,350
But…

790
01:04:15,190 --> 01:04:16,650
I realized it at that moment.

791
01:04:24,490 --> 01:04:25,490
"Goodbye."

792
01:04:27,070 --> 01:04:31,410
My death was a very fortunate death,

793
01:04:33,040 --> 01:04:37,330
as it allowed me time
to say my last goodbyes.

